Execution policy bypass = Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass


------------GitHub-----------------

Clone the project : git clone https://github.com/username/repo-name.git

Stage changes : git add .
Commit with a message : git commit -m "Added login form"
Push to GitHubv: git push origin main  # or whatever branch you're on

Before working every day, pull new changes : git pull origin main


-----------GitHub Branch---------------------

Create and Switch to a Branch for changes you are unsure : git checkout -b feature/chat-ui

Stage, Commit, Push the Branch : git add .
                                git commit -m "Built initial chat UI"
                                git push origin feature/chat-ui
Go to your repo → Click "Compare & Pull Request"
Target : feature/chat-ui → main

Merge to main Only When Ready : git checkout main
                                git pull origin main
                                git merge feature/chat-ui
                                git push origin main


Optional: Delete the branch after merge : git branch -d feature/chat-ui         # local
                                          git push origin --delete feature/chat-ui   # remote 


------roll back--------------
un-commit but keep the changes : git reset --soft HEAD~1